    "The essence of parameter estimation is to find the mapping from the received echo signal to the parameter space, and a widely used performance metric is the mean square error (MSE) between the estimated value and the ground truth.",
    "For any unbiased estimation of the deterministic parameter, its MSE is lower bounded by the Cramer-Rao bound (CRB) [88].",
    "Communication systemsWireless communication, as another typical application of the electromagnetic wave, aims to deliver the information with a high transmission rate and quality [89].",
